Valid bundle for a DSSE-content envelope whose Rekor v1 entry is a
hashedrekord (kind=hashedrekord, version=0.0.1) instead of dsse/intoto.
The hashedrekord's `data.hash` commits to SHA256(PAE(payloadType, payload))
— the same bytes the DSSE signature covers. This combination is allowed
by the Sigstore client spec
(https://github.com/sigstore/architecture-docs/blob/main/client-spec.md
"Bundle content vs. Rekor entry kind") and is useful for Rekor v2
deployments that only support the hashedrekord type, but here it's
exercised on Rekor v1.

Signed against production Sigstore Public Good (Fulcio + Rekor v1) with
sigstore-go's experimental hashedrekord-over-DSSE flag enabled, using the
sigstore-conformance/extremely-dangerous-public-oidc-beacon workflow
identity. No custom trusted_root.json is shipped; the test uses the
default production trust root.
